President Trump delivered remarks in the Rose Garden on June 16, 2020, announcing the signing of an executive order aimed at improving police standards and accountability. The President emphasized the importance of law enforcement in maintaining safety and order, while also acknowledging the need for reform and addressing concerns raised by the recent protests following the death of George Floyd. The executive order encourages police departments to adopt high professional standards, bans chokeholds except in life-threatening situations, and promotes the sharing of information about officers with significant issues. The President also mentioned his administration's achievements in criminal justice reform, job creation, and economic growth, and expressed optimism about the development of a vaccine for COVID-19.